      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 27 March 1889. ¶ H. Moors Esq. ¶ Acting Undersecretary. ¶ Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">89.03.27</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Moors</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">M89/4424, unit 421, VPRS 3992/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found; MS is a copy presumably made at the Chief Secretary's Office.</p>
               </note>Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">27 March 1889.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">H. Moors Esq.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Acting Undersecretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In accordance with your circular 2138, dated 25 March,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Circular not found.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I have the honor to submit in duplo herewith an estimate of the expenditure for such public works, buildings and repairs, as I deem requisite during the finance-year of 1889-1890 in the Government Botanists Department.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 17 April 1889,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Under Secretary, T. Wilson, noted: 'For submission to the Minister'. The Chief Secretary, A. Deakin, added the same day: 'Print'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The amount requested was included in the Estimates for 1889-90, under<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>'Sundry works, Melbourne'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Estimates of the revenue and expenditure for the year ending 30th June 1890</seg>, Parliamentary paper 1889.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>B 5,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 76).The item<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>at £180<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>included as 'Fittings and repairs at the Botanic Museum' in the list of works<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>approved<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>when the vote for the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Commissioner<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of Public Works<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was passed on the Legislative Assembly on 15 October 1889 (Victoria<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Votes and proceedings of the Legislative Assembly</seg>, session 1889, vol. 1,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>p. 224).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The work<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was evidently not carried out as the same amount<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for the same project<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was submitted<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Estimates in the following year;<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>see M to T. Wilson, 25 March 1890,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and notes thereto.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir, your obed. servant,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>signed ferd von Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Gov. Botanist</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Estimate of public works, buildings and repairs of the Govt. Botanists Department during the finance-year 1889-1890.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Addition and Repairs to the botanic Museum<space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>£180.- .-<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">The</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">projected expenditure</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">has been</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>marked with double lines in the margin.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">signed ferd von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Gov. Botanist</p>
         </div>
      </body>
